Heat some olive oil in a pan and fry the ginger, garlic and chopped chilli.Add the zest and juice of the lime and pour in the soy sauce.  Add the maple syrup and cook for 1 minute or until reduced and sticky.Meanwhile, pan-fry the two pieces of salmon for 2 minutes each side in a hot griddle pan.When the sauce is reduced add the salmon to the teriyaki sauce frying pan.Cook and drain the noodles, adding the sesame oil, seasoning and coriander and a squeeze of lime.  Serve the salmon on a bed of noodles with more chopped coriander.